issue.title: RateMyProfessor metrics caching in SQLite DB
issue.body: The metrics overall quality, difficulty, average sentiment, and take again percentage would be cached in the SQLite DB under the professor's name along with the time that the metrics were cached. Every time the RateMyProfessor information for a professor is required, there are two possible paths the program could take. If the metrics were cached more than a week ago, then RateMyProfessor is scraped and the metrics and last updated time are updated. Otherwise, the program just uses the cached data.

issue.title: Rewrote backend with promises instead of callbacks
issue.body:
Major rewrite of algorithm.js. 
Removed almost all callbacks in favor of using promises. 
Switched HTML request dependency from Request to node-fetch. 
Fixed how the algorithm gets the average rating from RateMyProfessors. 
Switched almost all instances of anonymous function declaration to use arrow functions.
